nodes.text: Zal Dinnes was a human female pilot who served in the Alliance to Restore the Republic. During the Galactic Civil War Lieutenant Dinnes was assigned to the Tierfon launch base as a member of the Tierfon Yellow Aces starfighter squadron. When encroaching Imperial patrols forced the rebels to scuttle the base and the Yellow Aces to be disbanded, Dinnes, along with Jek Tono Porkins and two other pilots were transferred to the Rebel base on Yavin 4 where Dinnes and Porkins were assigned to Red Squadron, with Dinnes obtaining the callsign Red Eight. She was shot down and died during the Battle of Yavin.

Zal Dinnes was a human female with blonde hair and hazel eyes. Dinnes had "V"s inside the yellow dots that ran along her helmet that indicated enemy fighter kills. Each mark equaled 20 enemy fighters that she killed in battle.
As a rebel pilot, Dinnes flew a T-65B X-wing starfighter. During the Battles of Scarif and Yavin, she wore a flight suit and a helmet with red and orange markings.

Zal Dinnes was portrayed by Zarene Dallas in Rogue One: A Star Wars Story, but her role was not listed in the end credits.[source?] The character was revealed on October 15, 2016 by Entertainment Weekly in an exclusive trading card from Star Wars: Card Trader.
